        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: stabilize auth loading states",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- What changed: stabilized protected-route loading so unresolved auth/profile data stays in route-shaped skeletons instead of briefly rendering signed-out, empty, or permission-denied states.\n- Why: auth/profile resolution and route data queries could complete in different frames, so pages sometimes rendered intermediate states before the real content.\n\n## Linked Issue\n\n- Related #\n\n## Screenshots\n\nTransient loading behavior was verified with route tests and a local protected-route smoke pass rather than static screenshots.\n\n- [x] Screenshots/recordings attached, or `N/A`\n\n## Behavioural Proof\n\nCovered `/dashboard`, `/settings`, `/stars`, `/import`, and `/management` locally. Protected routes now keep skeletons up until auth/profile and the first required user-scoped queries have resolved, and user-scoped queries skip until a current user exists.\n\n- [x] Behavioural proof included, or `N/A`\n\n## Security / Trust Impact\n\n- [x] No security/trust impact\n\n## Data / Deploy Impact\n\n- [x] No data/deploy impact\n\n## Verification\n\n- [x] `bun run ci:static`\n- [x] Focused tests for touched behavior: `bun run test -- src/lib/useAuthStatus.test.tsx src/routes/-dashboard.test.tsx src/routes/-settings.test.tsx src/routes/-stars.test.tsx src/__tests__/import.route.test.tsx src/routes/cli/-auth.test.tsx src/routes/docs/-auth.test.tsx src/routes/-management.test.tsx`\n- [x] Focused publish route tests: `bun run test -- src/__tests__/skills-publish-route.test.tsx`\n- [x] `bun run ci:unit`\n- [x] Broader gate when required: `bunx tsc --noEmit --pretty false`\n- [x] Other: local Playwright protected-route smoke; public PR preflight on a clean temp clone based on current `upstream/main`\n",
